          "text": "usp_ProcessChangePriorNewActiveStatusToActive",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to update the status of accounts and meters that were newly created in a prior billing cycle to an active status. Specifically, it changes the status from a temporary \"new active\" status (coded as '46') to a permanent \"active\" status (coded as 'AC'). This transition occurs after the new active status has been in place for one billing cycle. The procedure updates both the "
        },
